    &lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 12px;  padding-left: 12px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;JavaScript Weekly&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180785/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/r2fpf9tqoyfd43aqs1pc.jpg" width="640" style="    line-height: 100%;       "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180785/rss" title="tanstack.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.4em;"&gt;TanStack Hotkeys: A Type-Safe, Cross-Platform Hotkey¬†Library&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180786/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;TanStack family&lt;/a&gt; gains a new member: &lt;em&gt;Hotkeys&lt;/em&gt;, an alpha-stage universal keyboard interaction toolkit. It handles cross-environment quirks, supports multi-step sequences (like Vim commands or cheat codes), and can record user shortcuts. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180787/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Here's the full¬†pitch.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;TanStack LLC &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üí° Being in alpha, the focus in the docs is on React for now, but it's not React only, and they're looking for help with Solid, Angular, Svelte, and Vue¬†adapters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180784/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/c_limit,w_480,h_480,q_auto/copm/8572b4a4.png" width="110" height="110" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-left: 12px;     line-height: 100%;    "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180784/rss" title="" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Still Writing Tests Manually? Meticulous AI Is¬†Here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Notion, Dropbox, Wiz, and LaunchDarkly have found a new testing paradigm - and they can't imagine working without it. Built by ex-Palantir engineers, Meticulous autonomously creates a continuously evolving suite of E2E UI tests that delivers near-exhaustive coverage with zero developer¬†effort.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Meticulous &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180788/rss" title="devblogs.microsoft.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Announcing TypeScript 6.0 Beta&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî v6.0 is largely a &lt;em&gt;‚Äútime to clean up your tsconfig‚Äù&lt;/em&gt; release, designed to bridge the transition to the &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180789/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Go-powered native TypeScript 7&lt;/a&gt; later this year. Be aware of some tweaks, like &lt;code&gt;types&lt;/code&gt; defaulting to &lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;--strict&lt;/code&gt; now being true by default, among &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180790/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;many more breaking changes and¬†deprecations.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Microsoft &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN BRIEF:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìä Hot on the heels of the recent State of JS survey results come the &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180791/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;&lt;em&gt;State of React&lt;/em&gt; results.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ü§ñ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180792/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Google shows off a preview of WebMCP&lt;/a&gt;, an attempt to create a standard way for web sites to offer up abilities for AI agents to use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEASES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180793/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Biome 2.4&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì The formatting/linting tool can now handle embedded CSS &amp;amp; GraphQL in JS files, improves Vue and Svelte support, and adds HTML accessibility linting¬†rules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180794/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;React Native 0.84&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Hermes V1 is now the default JS engine on iOS and Android, iOS ships with precompiled binaries, and React¬†19.2.3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180795/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Node.js 25.6.1 (Current)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180796/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Node.js 24.13.1 (LTS)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180797/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;sql.js v1.14.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì SQLite compiled to JavaScript.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üìñ¬† Articles and Videos&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180798/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/b4fz0lk01ql1hz0cjaj5.jpg" width="640" style="    line-height: 100%;     "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180798/rss" title="aziis98.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Experiments with CodeMirror&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180799/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;CodeMirror&lt;/a&gt; is one of the most robust code editor components out there &lt;em&gt;(we‚Äôve just used it while rebuilding our newsletter editor!)&lt;/em&gt; and it‚Äôs very &lt;em&gt;extensible&lt;/em&gt; too, as seen in this walkthrough of building a VSCode-like ‚Äòchange review‚Äô feature for¬†it.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Antonio De Lucreziis &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180800/rss" title="nodejsdesignpatterns.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;How to Make an HTTP Request in Node.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A comprehensive guide to using &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; in production, tackling timeouts, streaming requests and responses, retries, concurrency, mocking, and more. Most of this is useful in the broader JavaScript¬†context.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Luciano Mammino &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180801/rss" title="www.tigerdata.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;One Database for Transactions and Analytics. No Pipelines&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî TimescaleDB extends Postgres so analytics runs on live data‚Äîno sync lag, no drift, no second system. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180801/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Try¬†free&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Tiger Data (creators of TimescaleDB) &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180802/rss" title="rednegra.net" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Implementing Virtual Scrolling at Billion-Row Scale&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A walkthrough of tackling the numerous challenges involved in building a table component (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180803/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;HighTable&lt;/a&gt;) that handles billions of¬†rows.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Sylvain Lesage &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180804/rss" title="sgom.es" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;JS-Heavy Approaches Aren't Compatible with Long-Term Performance Goals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A web performance engineer at Automattic makes the case against JS-heavy architectures and in support of a more server-centric¬†approach.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;S√©rgio Gomes &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180805/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Fun with TypeScript Generics&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Not your typical entry-level tutorial but a dive into a niche use¬†case. &lt;cite&gt;Adam Rackis&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180806/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Building Bulletproof React Components&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Elegant, no-nonsense tips from the co-creator of &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180807/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;SWR&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;cite&gt;Shu Ding&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180808/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;How Rolldown Works: High-Performance Code Splitting with Bitset¬†Logic&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;cite&gt;Atriiy&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180809/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Angular Bindings: What Are They and How Do I Use Them?&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;cite&gt;Bo French&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üõ†¬†Code &amp;amp; Tools&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180810/rss" title="blackboard.sh" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Electrobun v1: A Bun-Based Desktop App Approach&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî An introduction to a cross-platform runtime for JS/TS desktop apps. It uses the OS‚Äôs default web renderer (like &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180811/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Neutralinojs&lt;/a&gt;) with &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180812/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Bun&lt;/a&gt; as the engine and bundler behind the scenes. The resulting bundles are as small as¬†12MB. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180837/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Homepage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180838/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;GitHub repo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Blackboard &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üí° Electrobun's creator &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180813/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 600;"&gt;‚ñ∂Ô∏è shows it off in this 4 minute video.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180814/rss" title="console-ninja.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Console Ninja: Inline Logs &amp;amp; Smarter Debugging&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî See console output, runtime data, and errors next to your code, shared with your AI. Rethought, redesigned, and rebuilt in v2 for faster JavaScript debugging¬†workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Wallaby Team &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180815/rss" title="github.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;fetch-network-simulator: Intercept &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; to Simulate Poor Network¬†Conditions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The heart of this is a library that intercepts &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; and applies rules to do things like drop random requests, delay them, or slow them down, so you can see how resilient your app¬†is.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Karn Pratap Singh &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

