&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180133/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/m5tsifeulkmhzs7cllzp.jpg" width="640" style="      line-height: 100%;     "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180133/rss" title="www.heatjs.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Heat.js 5.0: A Flexible Heat Map Rendering Solution&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Generate customized interactive heatmaps (think GitHub contributions graph), or render heatmaps as &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180134/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;lines&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180135/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;bar charts&lt;/a&gt;. The site is &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180136/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;packed with demos&lt;/a&gt; to enjoy. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180137/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;GitHub¬†repo.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;William Troup &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180138/rss" title="workos.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Building an MCP Server? Don't Roll Your Own Auth&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî WorkOS AuthKit handles OAuth 2.1 flows so your MCP server just verifies tokens. Control which tools AI agents¬†access.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;WorkOS &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;üïí&lt;/span&gt;¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180139/rss" title="croner.56k.guru" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Croner 10.0: Cron-Style Triggers and Evaluation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Trigger functions on any cron schedule using &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180140/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;cron syntax.&lt;/a&gt; It can also evaluate cron expressions to give you a list of upcoming times. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180141/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;v10.0&lt;/a&gt; brings full OCPS (Open Cron Pattern Specification) 1.4 compliance and even more scheduling¬†options.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Hexagon &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;üóìÔ∏è&lt;/span&gt;¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180142/rss" title="dayflow-js.github.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;DayFlow: A Full Calendar Component for React&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A React-only feature-rich calendar component with drag-and-drop, multiple views, and all the usual GCal-style richness. Its infinite scrolling feature is nifty. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180143/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;GitHub¬†repo.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;DayFlow Contributors &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180144/rss" title="tsonic.org" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Tsonic: A TypeScript to C# Transpiler&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The idea is for creating native executables that run on .NET. I‚Äôve not tested it as I‚Äôm not in that ecosystem but it‚Äôs an interesting¬†idea.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Jeswin &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180145/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;EmbedPDF 2.4&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Framework-agnostic JavaScript PDF viewer. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180146/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180147/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;JavaScriptKit v0.40&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Swift framework for interacting with JS via¬†WASM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180148/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;StackBlur.js 3.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Long-standing Gaussian blur library; now using¬†ESM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180149/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Knip 5.83&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Finds and fixes unused files, dependencies and¬†exports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180150/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;jsPDF 4.1&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Generate PDFs directly in JavaScript. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180151/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180152/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;qrcode.vue 3.8&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Vue.js component to generate QR¬†codes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180153/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;focus-trap 8.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Trap focus within a DOM node. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180154/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üì¢¬† Elsewhere in the ecosystem&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some other interesting tidbits in the broader landscape:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180155/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/mhyuenl5ei607bgdn0ly.jpg" width="640" style="    line-height: 100%;         "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180155/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;GitHub is exploring solutions to tackle low-quality contributions&lt;/a&gt;, which could include giving you the option to disable PRs entirely or at least restrict them to collaborators. Got opinions? Join the¬†discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180156/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;How to throttle individual network requests&lt;/a&gt; in Chrome, rather than at a global level. Ideal for testing what happens when your dependencies load very¬†&lt;em&gt;slooooooowwwwwly....&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ü§ñ OpenAI has released &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180157/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;a desktop version of its agentic-coding &lt;em&gt;Codex&lt;/em&gt; app&lt;/a&gt;. macOS only for now, though someone &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180158/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;used Codex to port itself to Linux..&lt;/a&gt;¬†üòÇ&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ö†Ô∏è If you're a Windows user using the popular &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180159/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Notepad++&lt;/a&gt; editor, you might want to double check your install as the project &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180160/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;suffered a suspected state-sponsored hijack&lt;/a&gt; in¬†2025.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180161/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;svelteesp32&lt;/a&gt; is a curious project for embedding Svelte, React, Angular or Vue frontends into ESP32 microcontroller¬†apps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
